</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,799,824]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[282,500,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Gelechia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dryosyrta">
<emphasis box="[282,500,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">Gelechia dryosyrta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a single male collected in North-Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1219,1280,799,824]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">India</collectingCountry>
. The adult of 
<typeStatus box="[151,252,836,861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">holotype</typeStatus>
, its male genitalia in lateral view and the label were illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Clarke" box="[988,1146,836,861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" refString="Clarke, J. F. G. (1969) Catalogue of the type specimens of Microlepidoptera in the British Museum (Natural History) described by Edward Meyrick. 7. Trustees British Museum, London, 531 pp." type="book" year="1969">
Clarke (
<number box="[1078,1139,836,861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" value="1969.0">1969</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Additional material from the 
<typeStatus box="[197,245,872,896]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">type</typeStatus>
locality including female is required to provide clearer diagnosis and clarify the position of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Kiwaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dryosirta" subGenus="Empista">
<emphasis box="[1355,1382,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">K.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1402,1427,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">E.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[151,254,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">dryosirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within 
<taxonomicName box="[339,420,909,932]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Kiwaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[339,420,909,932]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">Kiwaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
